<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: new UO, is it time to go back?!</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Jomo">Jomo</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 7:17 p.m. 15/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: new UO, is it time to go back?!<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/rallos_zek.cgi?read=109" TARGET=_self>new UO, is it time to go back?!</A> (Enigma)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>I'm sort of looking at it this way for now:

<BR>You have to put your time in (gettin to lev 50) to learn the ropes, and prove that you want it bad enough to spend gobs of time hitting auto-attack and running back and forth to town etc. Once enough people hit lev 50, the game will begin. That's why we're on Ralloz Zek. It will still be hack and slash, but it will be versus players, and there is the potential for a lot of fun bloodshed. I'm also hoping that since Verant has paid staff, and every reason to want people to enjoy the game, they will make changes according to popular demand.
<BR>If not, then the next game will..
<BR>just two more cents.
<P>&gt; I did give EQ a try, it is a good looking
<BR>&gt; game more suitable for pals who like
<BR>&gt; first-person shooters like Qk etc., hack,
<BR>&gt; hack & slash slash ... no matter how we
<BR>&gt; try to justify it that is what it is! Think
<BR>&gt; about it bro...
<BR>&gt; Even the grouping has no real function but
<BR>&gt; to gang up on something more powerful when
<BR>&gt; it all comes down to it. PKing make no real
<BR>&gt; sense either with the way this game is
<BR>&gt; played! Finally, I found the game impersonal
<BR>&gt; & cold, with no real trade/skill system,
<BR>&gt; no real sense of community (trying to do it
<BR>&gt; you need $ & exp. points = hack &
<BR>&gt; slash all over again to get it!) anyway I
<BR>&gt; suspect that the novelty will soon wear out
<BR>&gt; & many pals will found out how boring
<BR>&gt; all these could get. Well, we will see,
<BR>&gt; sorry to say that: (
<BR>&gt; I really hoped that this game would replace
<BR>&gt; UO for me! Mean time, I am going back to
<BR>&gt; playing UO again (I still stay on EQ but not
<BR>&gt; as much as I like!), with all the new
<BR>&gt; changes happening to UO (i.e., with the
<BR>&gt; Evils vs. Heroes system now in testing, new
<BR>&gt; adjustments to the spell/weapon system or
<BR>&gt; the permanent murderer counter soon in place
<BR>&gt; and all other new cool stuff etc.) I bet it
<BR>&gt; will be fun to play it once again.
<P>&gt; P.s. I urge all pals to go to UO web site
<BR>&gt; & read about all the new cool stuff in
<BR>&gt; development/testing!
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
